However Origi has watched closely and believes his parent club will hit form soon.

'It's a new era at Liverpool and everything will go well. They have a fantastic team: Balotelli is a great striker, they have Daniel Sturridge and they have Raheem Sterling - one of the best young talents in the world.

'It's only positive and I don't think we have to worry about Liverpool.'

